HEADWORD: Inferable
<hw>In*fer"a*ble</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n*f⟦etil⟧r"⟦adot⟧*b'l ⟦or⟧
⟦icr⟧n*f⟦ecr⟧r"-; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of being
inferred or deduced from premises.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>inferrible</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>H. Spencer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A sufficient argument . . . is <qex>inferable</qex> from these
premises.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inference</ent>⟦br⟧
